Package: pigauto
Title: Phylogenetic Imputation via Graph Autoencoders
Version: 0.3.3
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "itchyshin@gmail.com")
Description: Imputes missing species trait data via a gated ensemble of a
    phylogenetic baseline and an attention-based graph neural network
    correction. For continuous, count, and ordinal traits the baseline is
    Brownian motion (via Rphylopars); for binary and categorical traits it
    is phylogenetic label propagation. The two predictors are blended by a
    per-trait gate that is calibrated on a held-out validation set, so when
    the baseline is already optimal the neural correction is zeroed out.
    Features conformal prediction intervals with guaranteed coverage for
    continuous/count/ordinal traits and adaptive spectral encoding that
    scales with tree size. Supports continuous, binary, categorical,
    ordinal, and count traits in a unified latent space, with optional
    multiple observations per species. Includes both a 300-species AVONET
    bird morphology subset and the full 9,993-species AVONET + BirdTree
    bundled datasets for examples and scale benchmarks.
